### Interview Insight

"What is the difference between authentication and authorization?" — Authentication verifies *who you are* (login with credentials, JWT verification). Authorization verifies *what you are allowed to do* (role check, ownership check). A user can be authenticated (valid JWT) but not authorized (trying to access another user's data). Always check both.

