### Interview Insight

"How does Node.js cluster mode work and why does it help?" — Node.js runs on a single CPU core by default. The `cluster` module forks the master process N times (one per core). All worker processes share the same TCP port — the master distributes incoming connections round-robin among workers. PM2 in cluster mode does this automatically. On an 8-core server, this gives roughly 8x throughput for I/O-bound workloads. CPU-bound work should use worker threads instead (cluster helps with I/O concurrency, not CPU parallelism).
